7:
Looks like I've drawn the winning the
hand!
11:
Embrace the BEAUTY of your
inevitable death!
15:
And that's more or less how things
are done!
23:
That's the something-or-other
Quartz, right? I went and got it for
you—okay, some of the others might
have helped too, but I held onto it!
27:
There's no doubt about it. Counting
Luca's, we now have a hold of all
three crystals.
35:
Come... to me.
If you do so, I will grant you...
everything.
42:
This little black box I got before the
mission... It... It sounds like it's
SPEAKING!
48:
Cap'n... the enemy... They're here!
They've—
64:
A true knight... stands firm... even
before—
69: I won't let you harm him!
80:
*pant*
There's simply no end to them!
87:
It's no use just healing others, I'll
never be able to keep up...
89: I will join the fight myself!
92:
Nay, my lady! If you should fall, who
would watch over and mend the
wounded? Please, allow me to—
95:
Sir Gerard?
Are my eyes deceiving me?
98:
Now why exactly would you be here
of all places? I heard you had
disappeared alongside the oracle.
101:
No... Upon closer inspection, you are
most certainly not the real Sir
Gerard.
107:
My apologies—I may have led you to
believe that this is of concern to me.
It is not.
Die.
115: And just in the nick of time, too!
119:
Good job holdin' out this long.
We've got this from here!
125:
You seem to have misunderstood
the situation.
139:
Hah-hah. He's a cutie, isn't he? Such
a thin, delicate little neck on
him—the type to suddenly snap in
even the gentlest breeze.
141:
I'm sure you too would hate to see
that happen.
146:
All right, we get it.
I'll give you the Genome Quartz.
150:
Captain Zegra's treasure is yours to
have—but you HAVE to give us the
boy first.
154:
Hmm... As dull a reaction as I should
have expected.
161:
Farewell, Crimson Blades.
I'm afraid I don't have time to waste
dealing with the likes of you.
163: I've already gotten everything I need!
167:
An elemental grenade! Be careful,
the flash won't go away any time
soon!
170:
O Sacred Light, listen to me!
Withdraw from this place at once!
182:
I heard the sound of an engine a
moment ago—they must be getting
away by ship!
187: Gah! I've had enough of this!
192:
I see it! Enemy vessel spotted, just
off port!
197:
Light the Alchemical Engine! Full
speed ahead! Don't let them get
away.
201:
But Cap'n, we just installed that on
the ship when we got to this island!
We haven't even tested it yet!
204:
We don't have any other options!
Without it, we'll never catch up to
that woman.
207:
Luca... He rode on this ship with all
the rest of us. That makes him a
Crimson Blade in my eyes!
209:
Are we going to give up on one of
our own?! I think not!
214:
You heard her, men! Fire up the
engine!
218:
Aren't you worried about what might
happen to Luca if we get too close?
That woman might...
221:
I don't think he's just a hostage to
her. I don't know why exactly, but I'm
pretty sure she was after Luca the
whole time.
224:
I can't believe I let her take the real
treasure from right under my nose...
231:
Yes! We're bringing Luca back in one
piece, no matter what it takes!
234:
We're pirates, after all! We're not
letting anyone run away with our
treasure!
